# Walkthrough: Rooms, Auth, Chat History, Friends & Call Logs

## Summary

Transformed the ephemeral WebSocket chat app into a full-featured platform with persistent storage, user accounts, rooms, DMs, friend lists, and call logs.

**Build status**: ✅ TypeScript compiles with zero errors | ✅ Prisma client generates successfully

---

## Database Schema (PostgreSQL + Prisma)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    User ||--o{ RoomMember : "is member of"
    User ||--o{ Message : "sends"
    User ||--o{ Friendship : "requests/receives"
    User ||--o{ CallLog : "makes/receives"
    Room ||--o{ RoomMember : "has members"
    Room ||--o{ Message : "contains"

    User {
        string id PK
        string username UK
        string email UK
        string passwordHash
        datetime createdAt
    }
    Room {
        string id PK
        string name
        boolean isGroup
        datetime createdAt
    }
    RoomMember {
        string id PK
        string userId FK
        string roomId FK
        datetime joinedAt
    }
    Message {
        string id PK
        string content
        string senderId FK
        string roomId FK
        datetime createdAt
    }
    Friendship {
        string id PK
        string requesterId FK
        string addresseeId FK
        enum status
        datetime createdAt
    }
    CallLog {
        string id PK
        string callerId FK
        string calleeId FK
        datetime startedAt
        datetime endedAt
        int duration
        string status
    }
```

